725303f-a.title: Queens: 39th Avenue - 60th Street
725303f-a.text:
39th Avenue, at the S.E. corner of 60th Street,
showing the Concord Democratic Club. The dwelling was
owned by J. Marc in 1891.
P. L. Sperr  June 23, I932
NO REPRODUCTIONS

725511f-a.title: Queens: 60th Street - 39th Avenue
725511f-a.text:
60th -treet, east side, just south of 39th Avenue, near the
Long Island Railroad bed, show'g two frame dwellings. The
Street was formely nawed 7th Street, in the village of Woodside.
P. L, Sperr  June 23, 1932
NO REPRODUCTIONS
